        <h1>About the SPLICE Catalog</h1>
        <p class="intro-text">
            The SPLICE Catalog is a central repository designed to support the Computer Science (CS) Education community by providing access to reusable smart learning content, standardized protocols, and rich learner datasets. 
            It aims to streamline the adoption of shared standards and facilitate data-driven research in CS education, data science, and learner sciences.
        </p>

        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
            The SPLICE project seeks to foster innovation and collaboration by:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Promoting the development and reuse of instrumented learning content for rich data collection.</li>
            <li>Providing formats and tools for analyzing learner data.</li>
            <li>Encouraging best practices in making learner data and analytics accessible to researchers.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What We Offer</h2>
        <p>
            The SPLICE Catalog provides resources and documentation to help educators, researchers, and developers integrate advanced learning technologies with ease. Key resources include:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Smart Learning Content organized by institution, domain, and type.</li>
            <li>Datasets for educational research and corresponding analytics tools.</li>
            <li>Standards and protocols like LTI, Caliper Analytics, xAPI, and PEML.</li>
            <li>Guides, tutorials, and examples for technology integration.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Community and Support</h2>
        <p>
            SPLICE fosters a collaborative community through working groups, Google Groups, and workshops. Whether you need technical assistance with LTI integration, help adopting interoperability standards, or advice on data analytics for education, the SPLICE community is here to support you.
        </p>

        <h2>Get Involved</h2>
        <p>
            To stay updated and participate in ongoing initiatives, you can:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Join the <a href="https://groups.google.com/g/cs-splice" target="_blank">SPLICE Google Group</a>.</li>
            <li>Explore our <a href="/catalog">SPLICE Catalog</a> of smart learning content and datasets.</li>
            <li>Check out tutorials, documentation, and best practices.</li>
            <li>Contact us at <a href="mailto:cssplice@gmail.com">cssplice@gmail.com</a> for inquiries.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
